magpie.data.utilities.splitters

Class AttributeIntervalSplitter

  • java.lang.Object
    • magpie.data.utilities.splitters.BaseDatasetSplitter
      • magpie.data.utilities.splitters.AttributeIntervalSplitter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, Commandable, Options, Printable

    public class AttributeIntervalSplitter
extends BaseDatasetSplitter
    This class splits data into multiple properties based on the attributes of each entry. User supplies the intervals, which are first sorting into ascending order. Then, the data is partitioned into bins with these points as edges.

    Usage: <attribute> <bin edges...>
    attribute: Name of attribute on which to split dataset
    bin edges...: Values on which to split data (i.e. "1" to split into (-Inf, 1) and [1, Inf])
